						               													<description>A primarily 2-player hex and counter game about Patton's September-December 1944 attempt to blast through the French Lorraine and get across the Siegfriend Line.  The possibility of Patton not having his supplies cut in October and getting the go-ahead to continue his September advance is a 33% playing option.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;(Battalion to) regiment to division level.  Weekly game-turns.  4.5 miles per hex.  115 units and pieces.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Features include Morning and Afternoon movement and attacks, deadly U.S. fighterbombers, inclement weather (like Morning Fog), special anti-tank tank destroyer battalion rules and movement, special armored cavalry group movement and combat abilities, German forest superiority, and (with time) French fort restoration.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;I have licensed Banner of War to publish PLC professionally - you can see the beautiful counter artwork in the latest image - so for the 4-year duration of our contract, its/my crude dtp version will NOT be free on my CoatneyHistory webpage to print off and play.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
